We are looking for the HIV Env protein, (group M subtype/clade A). The alphafold database and the pdb have no suitable structures. The PDB 6B0N is the closest, but it is too short, and has gaps and swaps relative to the DMS and alignment.

Hugh K Haddox, Adam S Dingens, Sarah K Hilton, Julie Overbaugh, Jesse D Bloom (2018) Mapping mutational effects along the evolutionary landscape of HIV envelope eLife 7:e34420 https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.34420
